article.headline: Centenary 83, Southeast Missouri State 51
article.story: FAIRBANKS, Alaska (AP) -- Larry Logan scored 16 points and pulled down 12 rebounds and Centenary defeated Southeast Missouri State 83-51 on Saturday in the consolation bracket of the BP Top of the World Classic. The Gents (2-2) ended a four-minute scoring drought on a basket by Lance Hill and took a 29-25 with 5:46 remaining in the first half. A 9-2 run gave Centenary a 43-32 halftime lead and the Gents pulled away in the second half with four players in double digits. Southeast Missouri (0-3) shot 31 percent from the field, including 6-for-25 on 3-pointers. Roderick Pearson scored the team's only 3-pointer in the second half with 53 seconds remaining. Centenary shot 46 percent from the field, including 10-for-22 on 3-point attempts. Brandon Foust scored nine points to lead the Redhawks. Tyrone Hamilton had 15 points for Centenary.
